### Solution:
The idea behind this solution is to first find the positions of the starting points. Then we loop through the array twice to calculate the shortest distance of each cell. 

The first loop does a breadth first search for the shortest distances of the starting points. The second loop updates the shortest distances if the cell is not a starting position.

This method can be further optimized since we only loop through the first two loops once, but it will not be an issue for a short code due to the memory constraints.

